Sentencas: Here, Sm1-xCaxBaCo2O5+delta (x = 0-0.4; SCBC) oxygen-deficient perovskites were synthesized by a sol-gel method and studied as potential novel cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Effect of calcium doping on Sm1-xCaxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: As an effective doping strategy, partial substitution of Ca for Sm in SmBaCo2O5+delta could reduce the thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) and improve the conductivity and catalytic activity of the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR).
Titulo: Effect of calcium doping on Sm1-xCaxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The x = 0-0.2 samples obtained after sintering at 1100 degrees C crystallized in an orthorhombic structure with the space group Pmmm and had good chemical compatibility with CeO2-based electrolytes at 1000 degrees C for 10 h. The TECs of the SCBC samples decreased from 20.2 x 10(-6) K-1 (x = 0) to 17.7 x 10(-6) K-1 (x = 0.2).
Titulo: Effect of calcium doping on Sm1-xCaxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area-specific resistances (ASRs) of the x = 0-0.4 cathodes were 0.163, 0.114, 0.075, and 0.090 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C. Additionally, the x = 0.2 cathode showed good electrochemical stability in a CO2 -containing atmosphere.
Titulo: Effect of calcium doping on Sm1-xCaxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: All results clearly indicated that double perovskite SCBC (x = 0-0.3) are promising cathode materials for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Effect of calcium doping on Sm1-xCaxBaCo2O5+δ cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
